Why is the old menu-based portal inefficient?
Traditional portals rely on hierarchical navigation, which assumes the user knows exactly where the developer hid the information

How will your AI empower humans rather than replace
them?

The goal isn't to take the wheel, but to be the copilot. AI empowers humans by shifting the focus from "low-value" tasks to "high-value" decision-making

Write three (3) User Stories using the format:
'As a [User], I want [AI Feature], so that [Benefit].'

As a Project Manager, I want a natural language summary of all overdue tasks across ten different departments, so that I can focus on resolving bottlenecks instead of manually generating status reports.

As a New Employee, I want to ask the portal "How do I set up my health benefits?" in plain English, so that I don't have to spend my first afternoon hunting through the HR policy handbook.

As a Customer Support Lead, I want AI to suggest relevant troubleshooting steps based on the customer's history, so that I can provide a more personalized and faster solution without searching through technical wikis.
